description.narrative: Partnerships continued to be strengthened with key institutions for data, research and evaluation production and use. These include the Central Statistics Agency (CSA), Policy Studies Institute and National Planning and Development Commission. Evidence was generated on child poverty, policy assessment and National Evaluation Capacity Assessment in partnership with these stakeholders respectively. Evidence and advocacy of their recommendations is promoting the linkages of research, evaluation, policy and programme implementation. In terms of national evaluation capacity development, UNICEF is supporting the African Evaluation Association Conference as part of a national organizing committee, and technically and financially supporting the Ethiopian Evaluation Association. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
